ZH: 我们应该节俭生活。
EN: We should live frugally.

ZH: 爷爷奶奶那一辈的人都很节俭。
EN: Our grandparents' generation are all very thrifty.

ZH: 节俭是美德。
EN: Frugality is a virtue.

ZH: 她的节俭令人钦佩。
EN: Her frugality is admirable.

ZH: 孩子们需要学会节俭。
EN: Children need to learn to be frugal.

ZH: 节俭是我们的传统美德。
EN: Frugality is our traditional virtue.

ZH: 他节俭地生活了一辈子。
EN: He lived frugally all his life.

ZH: 节俭可以让我们存下更多的钱。
EN: Frugality can help us save more money.

ZH: 节俭是我们家族的传统。
EN: Frugality is a tradition in our family.

ZH: 要保持节俭才能积累财富。
EN: Keeping frugal can help accumulate wealth.

ZH: 节俭是一种生活态度。
EN: Frugality is an attitude towards life.

ZH: 我们姐妹俩都很节俭。
EN: My sister and I are both frugal.

ZH: 学会节俭才能过好日子。
EN: Learning to be frugal is the key to a good life.

ZH: 节俭是一种生活方式。
EN: Frugality is a way of life.

ZH: 父母要给孩子树立节俭的榜样。
EN: Parents should set a frugal example for their children.

ZH: 节俭可以让我们更有责任感。
EN: Frugality can make us more responsible.

ZH: 她的节俭为家庭节省了不少开支。
EN: Her frugality has saved the family a lot of expenses.

ZH: 节俭是一种品格。
EN: Frugality is a character trait.

ZH: 要培养节俭的习惯。
EN: Cultivate the habit of frugality.

ZH: 她的节俭给她的生活带来了很多好处。
EN: Her frugality has brought her many benefits in life.
